		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 2/26/2004 10:48:09 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=67&FN=Paladin&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2129462&TN=agro+method&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2130905&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Disarm is a zero agro attack, in other words it will not generate any additional agro, or at least no measurable agro.</P><P>if you insist on using it though, then save yourself the hotkey and time, find out what number button it is on from the menu that generates the disarm, taunt etc buttons (alt-M) then make the following hotkey:</P><P>/doability 1 (where 1 is the button number for taunt)<BR>/doability 2 (where 2 is the number for Disarm)</P><P>If you are bashing with a shield or 2-hand bash, then you can also add that into the same button as well. I wouldn't bother though, disarm really has no agro effect.</P><P>Generally, though use your most mana efficient stuns for agro. Cease for pulling, since it generates agro, does no damage (so mob won't summon you) and has a zero duration. Once in camp, use the cheapest stun that will land and has a duration, especially right off the bat when it isn't slowed yet. You will want to favour stuns that have a duration, rather then spamming cease and desist, because you will mitigate a considerable amount of damage by having the mob stunned. The amount of stuns needed are dependent on how much agro is needed (some groups manage agro better then others, ala-wizard sho starts off by nuking the incoming critter) and how much mana you have available.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
