		<hr size="1">I couldn't agree more with that last paragraph.  Well written and exactly what I would do.</P><P>However, I disagree with the most of the rest of the post.  Every study I've seen, says that disarm does add to aggro.  But yes, it is minimal and usually just not worth it.  I suppose it doesn't hurt anything to tie it into Taunt...just doesn't seem worth it, since your hotkey doesn't grey out to let you know it's unavailable.  IMO, you need to know when it's available, and not to use it until needed.  Spamming the taunt key is just a waste of energy, and sets you up to not have it when needed.</P><P>To add bash to that is scary.  Bash, while adding some decent damage, sometimes, is best for interruptions on casters.  To again, not know when it's available or use it when not needed can be detrimental.</P><P>To each his own though.  I'm not saying you are wrong, just that I wouldn't do it that way...and the above are my reasons. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
