		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 3/8/2004 9:35:03 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=11082">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Kohinoor" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Kohinoor">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Kohinoor" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=67&FN=Paladin&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2129462&TN=agro+method&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2136228&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I use Stun to tag off the puller when I am MA.  It is useful because it has low mana consumption and high aggro component.  I am level 65 and fight fairly exclusively in PoP and GoD nowadays.  The great thing about using Stun to attract attention at this level is that it will be resisted, but still generates aggro.  You can literally watch the mob change course as it stops following the puller and starts running toward you instead.</P><P>After that, when the mob is up close and personal, I lead with a Taunt, hotly followed by alternating Akilae then Akera.  This is usually enough to keep attention on me while slowing happens.  After that I alternate between Akilae and Akera.  I use Akilae most for several reasons: it is more mana efficient than Akera, it is resisted less, and recast time is slightly faster.</P><P>On a multi-pull situation I will lead with an early Group Heal even though it is possible that nobody needs healing.  Wave of Marr (don't have Wave of Trushar yet) brings plenty of aggro.  All the MoBs will be on my tail, leaving the crowd control folks to do their thing without fear of interrupts.  Also, this means the healer only needs to focus on me rather than dividing their attention between MA, puller, and chanter.</P><P>Root aggro is sometimes useful too, especially Shackles of Tunare which I understand is the fastest Root spell in the game.</P><P>I realise many of the spells I've mentioned are a bit above your level right now, but hopefully it will trigger a few thoughts for you about trying different techniques with the spells you have on hand already.</P><P><a HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=558247&resize=true"> <img src="http://www.poutinet.com/sigs/KohiSig.jpg" border=0> </a></P><P>Message edited by: Kohinoor (3/8/2004 9:35:03 AM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
