		<hr size="1">/agree Kohi</P><P>I generally have FoAkilae, FoAkera, QWoSerenity, and Cease up. I like my stuns, as you can see. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>How I use them depends on the situation of course, but if I have adequate time, I'll use Cease to grab initial aggro off the puller. It goes just like Kohi described with Stun; even on a resist, he should come straight toward me.</P><P>As soon as the mob gets to me, I do the same as Kohi. I'll hit it with Akilae, generally followed immediately after with Akera. This serves not only to generate aggro, but to act as kind of a "ghetto slow" while the mob is being properly slowed. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>I keep serenity up mostly for positioning, but also because it's one of only two stuns that work on some mobs, such as "militis" and higher mobs in BoT (Akera should land on casters: tyv, hellig, etc.).</P><P>If I'm having more trouble than usual keeping aggro for whatever reason, I'll keep using Akera/Cease, even if they may not take effect.</P><P>Hmm, bit of a ramble...but nothing else to do while waiting for vkr in KC...I want my VP key! <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=199162">Occam</a><BR>Lord Protector of Tunare<BR>Zebuxoruk<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
