		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=49549">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Teluas Truesword" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Teluas+Truesword">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Teluas Truesword" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=67&FN=Paladin&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=2129462&TN=agro+method&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=2139138&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I never cast a single spell on a mob until it's almost on top of the camp.  In fact, I've gotten pretty good at timing the cast time of Akilae so that it lands right when the mob is in front of me. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle>  Then, I start melee and hit taunt right away.  This way I'm guaranteed on top of the aggro list (provided taunt is successful).  Then I let off 2-3 more stuns as they repop, and can then usually go afk for the rest of the fight if I want to.  <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>As far as positioning with stuns... who cares if the other melees bitch?  Screw em.  <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/wink.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle>  If you're tanking it's your job to make sure the mob is in the best tactical position available... and if that means pushing the mob around some, then do it.  I for one do whatever it takes to keep the mob in a good position so pets are on the rear and so I'm far enough away from any rooted/mezzed mobs to avoid any danger of mistargeting/waking up.  As a result, I sometimes move all over the place when I MT.  <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>Wave heals do generate aggro, but in my experience, they're not something to rely on for aggro unless you have a few party members getting beat on at the time you cast it.  And even then, if they've done more to a mob than you have, you still may not pull aggro.  For example, one of the shamen I group with a lot usually has 4-5 dots on any given mob at any given time... unless I'm right on top of things and chain stun my mana out, he usually ends up tanking.  heh</P><P>Hope that helps. <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle></P><P>Message edited by: Teluas Truesword (3/13/2004 2:10:04 PM)<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
